WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:11.136 --> 00:00:13.179 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
"Now, this country was divided:

00:00:13.263 --> 00:00:15.682 position:50% align:center
there was a left side
and a right side,

00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.809 position:50% align:center
and the two did not get along.

00:00:17.892 --> 00:00:20.478 position:50% align:center
So, they built a wall.

00:00:20.562 --> 00:00:22.564 position:50% align:center
They agreed that they
would keep to themselves

00:00:22.647 --> 00:00:24.274 position:50% align:center
and have no dealings
with each other.

00:00:24.357 --> 00:00:27.402 position:50% align:center
That way, the people of
both sides would be happy."

00:00:35.118 --> 00:00:36.369 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A]
Sometimes I wonder what

00:00:36.453 --> 00:00:38.371 position:50% align:center
the point of this thing is.

00:00:38.455 --> 00:00:41.791 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ] Isn't the "point" of a
wall fairly straightforward?

00:00:41.875 --> 00:00:43.335 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A] Well,
yes, it was originally built

00:00:43.418 --> 00:00:45.628 position:50% align:center
to keep the two sides apart
since they have no desire

00:00:45.712 --> 00:00:48.048 position:50% align:center
to interact, and it
certainly does that.

00:00:48.131 --> 00:00:49.716 position:50% align:center
But think of all
the opportunities

00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:51.259 position:50% align:center
we're missing with it here.

00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:52.552 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ]
Oh.

00:00:52.635 --> 00:00:53.762 position:50% align:center
We want to make sure

00:00:53.845 --> 00:00:55.764 position:50% align:center
we're still winning
against the other side.

00:00:55.847 --> 00:00:58.099 position:50% align:center
But how are we supposed to
prove to them that we're better

00:00:58.183 --> 00:01:00.810 position:50% align:center
than they are when this wall
prevents them from seeing us?

00:01:00.894 --> 00:01:02.145 position:50% align:center
Have any ideas that might

00:01:02.228 --> 00:01:03.980 position:50% align:center
help with our predicament,
madam witch?

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:07.317 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ]
Hm... Let me think.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:09.194 position:50% align:center
Do you happen to
have a knife, Sir?

00:01:09.277 --> 00:01:12.030 position:50% align:center
Ah... Oh, yes, right here.

00:01:13.615 --> 00:01:16.576 position:50% align:center
And what are you planning
to do with it, exactly?

00:01:17.952 --> 00:01:19.662 position:50% align:center
You'll see soon enough.

00:01:25.794 --> 00:01:29.464 position:50% align:center
Uh... Are you carving
words into it?

00:01:29.547 --> 00:01:32.092 position:50% align:center
"This side of the
country is great.

00:01:32.175 --> 00:01:34.552 position:50% align:center
By the Witch of the Travels."

00:01:34.636 --> 00:01:36.930 position:50% align:center
And what is the meaning
of this message?

00:01:37.013 --> 00:01:39.516 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ] Well, this wall
represents the rivalry

00:01:39.599 --> 00:01:41.101 position:50% align:center
between the left and right.

00:01:41.184 --> 00:01:43.311 position:50% align:center
But you also want it
to represent this side's

00:01:43.395 --> 00:01:46.147 position:50% align:center
superiority over the
other, do you not?

00:01:47.524 --> 00:01:48.775 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:01:48.858 --> 00:01:51.111 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ] My suggestion is,
you encourage travelers

00:01:51.194 --> 00:01:53.947 position:50% align:center
who visit to carve words
of praise into the wall.

00:01:54.030 --> 00:01:55.740 position:50% align:center
The more etchings on this side,

00:01:55.824 --> 00:01:58.576 position:50% align:center
the more it will prove that
it's favored over the other.

00:01:58.660 --> 00:02:00.537 position:50% align:center
Uh... I don't know--

00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:02.747 position:50% align:center
that's not really how we
do things around here.

00:02:02.831 --> 00:02:04.207 position:50% align:center
[NIKÉ]
That's too bad.

00:02:04.290 --> 00:02:06.167 position:50% align:center
Because I've already seen
the other side of the wall,

00:02:06.251 --> 00:02:07.877 position:50% align:center
and it's covered in
glowing remarks

00:02:07.961 --> 00:02:09.337 position:50% align:center
travelers have left
in their wake.

00:02:09.421 --> 00:02:11.881 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:11.965 --> 00:02:14.300 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] "After that,
I knew I had to quickly

00:02:14.384 --> 00:02:17.137 position:50% align:center
find my way to the other side."

00:02:17.220 --> 00:02:19.973 position:50% align:center
Oh, that's just too bad,
because I've seen the other side

00:02:20.056 --> 00:02:22.559 position:50% align:center
of the wall, and it's already
covered in glowing remarks

00:02:22.642 --> 00:02:23.977 position:50% align:center
travelers have left
in their wake.

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:25.520 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:02:25.603 --> 00:02:29.107 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] "So that I could give
them identical instructions.

00:02:29.190 --> 00:02:33.236 position:50% align:center
And thus, a brand new custom
for travelers was born.

00:02:33.319 --> 00:02:35.655 position:50% align:center
When they arrive in this
country, they pay a visit

00:02:35.739 --> 00:02:38.992 position:50% align:center
to the wall, and carve
their own words of praise."

00:04:16.464 --> 00:04:18.341 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] But why did it
matter if the travelers

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:20.885 position:50% align:center
carved words on the wall or not?

00:04:20.969 --> 00:04:22.387 position:50% align:center
Let me see.

00:04:22.470 --> 00:04:25.223 position:50% align:center
I suppose it was essentially
a popularity contest.

00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:26.641 position:50% align:center
Popularity contest?

00:04:26.725 --> 00:04:29.185 position:50% align:center
It's a way of choosing the
one that people like more.

00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.730 position:50% align:center
If one side had more etchings
than the other one did,

00:04:31.813 --> 00:04:33.523 position:50% align:center
then they could say they
had proof that travelers

00:04:33.606 --> 00:04:35.525 position:50% align:center
liked them better.
Does that make sense?

00:04:35.608 --> 00:04:37.819 position:50% align:center
Uh-huh. So, who won?

00:04:37.902 --> 00:04:40.071 position:50% align:center
Which of the sides turned out
to be more popular?

00:04:40.155 --> 00:04:41.364 position:50% align:center
And how many more nice words

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:43.992 position:50% align:center
did they have than
the other side did?

00:04:44.075 --> 00:04:45.493 position:50% align:center
That's something you'll
just have to go see

00:04:45.577 --> 00:04:47.704 position:50% align:center
with your own eyes, dear.

00:04:47.787 --> 00:04:52.000 position:50% align:center
When I become a great
traveling witch someday, I will!

00:04:53.001 --> 00:04:55.503 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Wow, this is amazing!

00:04:55.587 --> 00:04:58.381 position:50% align:center
"This country is the best!"

00:04:58.465 --> 00:05:01.468 position:50% align:center
"I've never been to
such a great country!"

00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:04.721 position:50% align:center
"We got engaged
in this spot today!"

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:07.265 position:50% align:center
"Best friends forever!"

00:05:07.349 --> 00:05:09.100 position:50% align:center
Whoa.

00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:13.146 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:05:13.229 --> 00:05:15.565 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Uh... Gross.

00:05:15.648 --> 00:05:17.484 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A]
Um, pardon me, miss.

00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:20.612 position:50% align:center
Would you happen to be the witch

00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:22.822 position:50% align:center
the United Magic
Association sent over?

00:05:22.906 --> 00:05:25.658 position:50% align:center
Yeah. I'm Saya,
the Charcoal Witch.

00:05:25.742 --> 00:05:27.744 position:50% align:center
It's a pleasure to
meet you, good sir!

00:05:27.827 --> 00:05:29.162 position:50% align:center
I've heard a lot
about this wall,

00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:32.248 position:50% align:center
but it's even more
amazing in person.

00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:34.292 position:50% align:center
It's fascinating to see
how many people enjoyed

00:05:34.376 --> 00:05:35.877 position:50% align:center
visiting this side
of the country.

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:37.879 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A] This
is the subject of our request.

00:05:37.962 --> 00:05:41.132 position:50% align:center
It is our hope that you can
do something different with it.

00:05:41.216 --> 00:05:42.759 position:50% align:center
Do something different?

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:44.094 position:50% align:center
The wall's been like this

00:05:44.177 --> 00:05:46.262 position:50% align:center
more than ten years,
ever since a traveling witch

00:05:46.346 --> 00:05:48.890 position:50% align:center
suggested we have
visitors leave messages.

00:05:48.973 --> 00:05:50.350 position:50% align:center
People seem to be
losing interest

00:05:50.433 --> 00:05:53.061 position:50% align:center
in the old tradition, and we
thought it might be time

00:05:53.144 --> 00:05:54.437 position:50% align:center
for something new.

00:05:54.521 --> 00:05:56.606 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
A new tradition, huh?

00:05:56.690 --> 00:05:57.857 position:50% align:center
I don't know.

00:05:57.941 --> 00:05:59.859 position:50% align:center
This one seems
pretty great to me.

00:05:59.943 --> 00:06:02.112 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's hard to imagine
something that would be

00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:05.615 position:50% align:center
a bigger draw than the famous
"wall etched by travelers."

00:06:06.700 --> 00:06:10.662 position:50% align:center
[SAYA gasps]
Travelers? Oh! I've got it!

00:06:10.745 --> 00:06:14.249 position:50% align:center
Do you happen to have a knife
I can borrow, please?

00:06:14.332 --> 00:06:16.751 position:50% align:center
Uh. Sure.

00:06:19.212 --> 00:06:21.965 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
I... L... Lo...

00:06:22.048 --> 00:06:23.550 position:50% align:center
Oh, wow, this is
actually a lot harder

00:06:23.633 --> 00:06:25.385 position:50% align:center
 than I thought
it was going to be.

00:06:25.468 --> 00:06:29.764 position:50% align:center
...ove... Elaina.

00:06:29.848 --> 00:06:31.850 position:50% align:center
I love Miss Elaina.
I love Miss Elaina.

00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:33.309 position:50% align:center
I love Miss Elaina.

00:06:33.393 --> 00:06:35.645 position:50% align:center
Miss Elaina, Miss Elaina,
Miss Elaina, Miss Elaina...

00:06:35.729 --> 00:06:38.440 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Just what do you
think you're doing?

00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:42.402 position:50% align:center
This wall was not built for you
to declare your carnal desires!

00:06:42.485 --> 00:06:43.445 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Excuse you!

00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:44.779 position:50% align:center
What do you think you're doing?

00:06:44.863 --> 00:06:46.698 position:50% align:center
Besides interrupting
very important work!

00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:47.907 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A]
What is so important about

00:06:47.991 --> 00:06:49.951 position:50% align:center
name carving?
This wall is a place

00:06:50.035 --> 00:06:51.953 position:50% align:center
for travelers to
commemorate their experience

00:06:52.037 --> 00:06:53.038 position:50% align:center
in this country!

00:06:53.121 --> 00:06:55.290 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Oh! So that's the rule?

00:06:55.373 --> 00:06:57.167 position:50% align:center
Then that's the change
you need to make!

00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:58.877 position:50% align:center
What?

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.587 position:50% align:center
Starting today,
it's not going to be

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:01.880 position:50% align:center
just for travelers anymore.

00:07:01.963 --> 00:07:04.799 position:50% align:center
Locals can carve
their sentiments, too.

00:07:04.883 --> 00:07:06.426 position:50% align:center
That's right! They can
carve their dreams

00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:08.720 position:50% align:center
or their crushes, they
can etch in things like:

00:07:08.803 --> 00:07:11.056 position:50% align:center
"I love Miss Elaina! So much."

00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:14.768 position:50% align:center
And what would be the
reason for doing that?

00:07:14.851 --> 00:07:17.562 position:50% align:center
Just think: the
citizens are the ones

00:07:17.645 --> 00:07:19.272 position:50% align:center
who wanted it in the
first place, right?

00:07:19.356 --> 00:07:20.690 position:50% align:center
Doesn't that mean they
should be the ones

00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.734 position:50% align:center
who get to enjoy it the most?

00:07:26.696 --> 00:07:29.157 position:50% align:center
Instead of being a wall that's
just meant for travelers,

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:31.618 position:50% align:center
make it something that
encourages those who live here

00:07:31.701 --> 00:07:33.578 position:50% align:center
to remember what's
most important to them.

00:07:33.661 --> 00:07:36.456 position:50% align:center
Interesting.

00:07:36.539 --> 00:07:38.416 position:50% align:center
[SAYA]
Thanks for this.

00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:40.669 position:50% align:center
I gotta run now, though.

00:07:40.752 --> 00:07:41.503 position:50% align:center
Right.

00:07:41.586 --> 00:07:42.671 position:50% align:center
It turns out I've got a job

00:07:42.754 --> 00:07:44.631 position:50% align:center
on the other side
of the wall, too!

00:07:44.714 --> 00:07:45.715 position:50% align:center
Whee!

00:07:57.560 --> 00:08:00.105 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] One might ask:
why is it that my heart

00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:03.400 position:50% align:center
was swelling with
anticipation on that day?

00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:06.653 position:50% align:center
The answer is: because I was
about to visit the country

00:08:06.736 --> 00:08:10.031 position:50% align:center
that had words etched into its
wall just as I had read about

00:08:10.115 --> 00:08:12.409 position:50% align:center
in <i>The Adventures of Niké</i> ,
the book that had meant

00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:14.661 position:50% align:center
so much to me
throughout my life.

00:08:14.744 --> 00:08:16.871 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:08:16.955 --> 00:08:18.832 position:50% align:center
What happened to the wall?

00:08:18.915 --> 00:08:21.084 position:50% align:center
[PEOPLE chattering]

00:08:21.167 --> 00:08:23.962 position:50% align:center
Would you like a souvenir
or two from your trip today?

00:08:24.045 --> 00:08:25.505 position:50% align:center
[PEDDLER GIRL 07C]
It's not just ordinary stone,

00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:27.507 position:50% align:center
it's debris from
our famous wall!

00:08:27.590 --> 00:08:30.135 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] No, debris from
a wall is still just debris.

00:08:30.218 --> 00:08:32.762 position:50% align:center
My! If it isn't
the traveling witch!

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:34.639 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07B]
It's been more than a decade!

00:08:34.723 --> 00:08:37.684 position:50% align:center
Forgive me, gentlemen,
but how do you know who I am?

00:08:37.767 --> 00:08:39.394 position:50% align:center
Your face actually
looks a bit younger

00:08:39.477 --> 00:08:40.687 position:50% align:center
than it did back then.

00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:42.063 position:50% align:center
I'll say.

00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:44.441 position:50% align:center
And that's not the only thing
different about you.

00:08:44.524 --> 00:08:45.567 position:50% align:center
I'll say.

00:08:45.650 --> 00:08:47.318 position:50% align:center
I suppose you aren't her.

00:08:47.402 --> 00:08:49.320 position:50% align:center
That's most unfortunate.

00:08:49.404 --> 00:08:51.865 position:50% align:center
Well, for a moment,
I thought the two of you

00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:54.409 position:50% align:center
might actually be officials
of this country,

00:08:54.492 --> 00:08:55.618 position:50% align:center
but perhaps I was wrong,

00:08:55.702 --> 00:08:57.704 position:50% align:center
and you're just a couple
of boorish old men.

00:08:57.787 --> 00:08:59.956 position:50% align:center
We are indeed this
country's officials.

00:09:00.040 --> 00:09:02.292 position:50% align:center
And I guess we're also
boorish old men.

00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:05.712 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] Uh... In any case,
maybe you can help me.

00:09:05.795 --> 00:09:07.547 position:50% align:center
See, I came to see
the famous wall,

00:09:07.630 --> 00:09:10.091 position:50% align:center
but it appears
to be in pieces now.

00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:11.760 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
The two gentleman then explained

00:09:11.843 --> 00:09:14.262 position:50% align:center
why the wall was now rubble.

00:09:14.346 --> 00:09:16.973 position:50% align:center
Apparently, another witch
had visited this country

00:09:17.057 --> 00:09:20.685 position:50% align:center
a little before I did, at her
advice, the citizens gained

00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:23.855 position:50% align:center
permission to carve anything
they wished into the wall.

00:09:23.938 --> 00:09:27.192 position:50% align:center
At first, they were overjoyed
with their new outlet,

00:09:27.275 --> 00:09:30.403 position:50% align:center
but as days passed,
and then weeks...

00:09:30.487 --> 00:09:31.988 position:50% align:center
[LOCAL 07A] Guess it wasn't
forever after all!

00:09:32.072 --> 00:09:33.698 position:50% align:center
Considering we broke up!

00:09:33.782 --> 00:09:37.118 position:50% align:center
[LOCAL 07A] I wrote what?
It's not even true! I was drunk!

00:09:37.202 --> 00:09:38.453 position:50% align:center
[LOCAL 07B]
What the hell?

00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:40.038 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] Travelers say,
"What happens on the trip,

00:09:40.121 --> 00:09:42.665 position:50% align:center
stays on the trip,"
then they move on.

00:09:42.749 --> 00:09:44.793 position:50% align:center
But when the etchings are
by and about the people

00:09:44.876 --> 00:09:47.712 position:50% align:center
who live there, their
permanence may transform

00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:51.049 position:50% align:center
into painful memories
that can't be escaped.

00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:53.093 position:50% align:center
[MAN 07A, WOMAN 07A gasp]

00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:54.344 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:09:54.427 --> 00:09:55.929 position:50% align:center
[MEN gasp]

00:09:56.012 --> 00:10:00.225 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] And so, they agreed it
was best to tear down the wall.

00:10:00.308 --> 00:10:02.435 position:50% align:center
Before they knew it,
the resentment they felt

00:10:02.519 --> 00:10:04.062 position:50% align:center
toward the people
on the other side

00:10:04.145 --> 00:10:06.189 position:50% align:center
didn't seem to exist anymore.

00:10:08.566 --> 00:10:10.318 position:50% align:center
Everybody here was completely

00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:12.487 position:50% align:center
convinced they were better
than those who resided

00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:13.738 position:50% align:center
on the other side of the wall.

00:10:13.822 --> 00:10:15.824 position:50% align:center
But then they saw all of
the embarrassing things

00:10:15.907 --> 00:10:17.617 position:50% align:center
they wrote themselves,
and they realized

00:10:17.701 --> 00:10:19.244 position:50% align:center
that wasn't the case after all.

00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.246 position:50% align:center
I guess it turns out
this country never

00:10:21.329 --> 00:10:23.707 position:50% align:center
even needed a wall
to begin with.

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:25.875 position:50% align:center
We've got more
in common than we knew.

00:10:25.959 --> 00:10:27.669 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07B] I
suspect we'll be quite content

00:10:27.752 --> 00:10:30.255 position:50% align:center
living peacefully in
our ordinary country.

00:10:30.338 --> 00:10:31.589 position:50% align:center
Ah...

00:10:31.673 --> 00:10:34.342 position:50% align:center
Now then, if you'll please
excuse us, madam witch.

00:10:34.426 --> 00:10:36.553 position:50% align:center
Um, before you go,

00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:38.680 position:50% align:center
would you mind telling me
which side had more praises

00:10:38.763 --> 00:10:42.142 position:50% align:center
etched into it before
the wall was torn down?

00:10:42.225 --> 00:10:43.643 position:50% align:center
Isn't that obvious?

00:10:43.727 --> 00:10:45.895 position:50% align:center
It was the same on both sides.

00:10:45.979 --> 00:10:47.397 position:50% align:center
The same?

00:10:47.480 --> 00:10:50.150 position:50% align:center
We were two halves
of a single country.

00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:51.609 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07B]
And we all worked equally hard

00:10:51.693 --> 00:10:53.403 position:50% align:center
not to lose the
silly competition

00:10:53.486 --> 00:10:55.196 position:50% align:center
we had with the other side.

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:57.157 position:50% align:center
But how could you compete
with the other side

00:10:57.240 --> 00:10:59.617 position:50% align:center
if you had no way of seeing how
much they were accomplishing

00:10:59.701 --> 00:11:01.411 position:50% align:center
and what you were up against?

00:11:01.494 --> 00:11:03.121 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07B] That's
how we convinced ourselves

00:11:03.204 --> 00:11:05.248 position:50% align:center
that we were better,
by refusing to look

00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:06.624 position:50% align:center
on the other side of the wall.

00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:07.709 position:50% align:center
[GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL 07A]
Yes, that was true

00:11:07.792 --> 00:11:09.461 position:50% align:center
for our side as well.

00:11:14.924 --> 00:11:17.969 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] I feel certain that
it worked out for the best.

00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:20.930 position:50% align:center
A country doesn't belong
to tourists or travelers.

00:11:21.014 --> 00:11:22.724 position:50% align:center
It's a home for those
who live there

00:11:22.807 --> 00:11:25.518 position:50% align:center
and they should
always take priority.

00:11:25.602 --> 00:11:27.103 position:50% align:center
I am disappointed
that I couldn't

00:11:27.187 --> 00:11:29.481 position:50% align:center
see the wall, of course.

00:11:29.564 --> 00:11:31.608 position:50% align:center
I wonder if Niké
carved those words

00:11:31.691 --> 00:11:33.651 position:50% align:center
knowing that doing so
would ultimately lead

00:11:33.735 --> 00:11:36.112 position:50% align:center
to the wall being torn down.

00:11:36.196 --> 00:11:38.365 position:50% align:center
No, there's no way.

00:11:38.448 --> 00:11:39.741 position:50% align:center
[PEDDLER GIRL 07B]
Hello, madam witch.

00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:42.452 position:50% align:center
Would you like a piece
of the wall as a souvenir?

00:11:42.535 --> 00:11:43.995 position:50% align:center
I might as well.

00:11:44.079 --> 00:11:46.331 position:50% align:center
I wonder which of
these I should pick.

00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:47.582 position:50% align:center
This one!

00:11:47.665 --> 00:11:49.084 position:50% align:center
Nice choice!

00:11:50.293 --> 00:11:52.087 position:50% align:center
Thanks for visiting!

00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:01.304 position:50% align:center
"Elai"...?

00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:20.490 position:50% align:center
Lovely. It looks like
we have yet another

00:12:20.573 --> 00:12:22.450 position:50% align:center
excellent harvest this year.

00:12:22.534 --> 00:12:25.161 position:50% align:center
These grapes are going to
make some delicious wine.

00:12:25.245 --> 00:12:26.871 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN]
Of course they are, Darling.

00:12:26.955 --> 00:12:29.165 position:50% align:center
I can't wait!

00:12:29.249 --> 00:12:31.876 position:50% align:center
[BOY 07A]
Grandpa! Look it!

00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:34.546 position:50% align:center
This is what I'm gonna wear for
the Grape-Throwing Festival!

00:12:34.629 --> 00:12:36.381 position:50% align:center
I like it. Looks
good on you, kid.

00:12:36.464 --> 00:12:39.342 position:50% align:center
[BOY 07A giggles]
Oh! Will you tell me the story

00:12:39.426 --> 00:12:41.845 position:50% align:center
of the very first
Grape-Throwing Festival again?

00:12:41.928 --> 00:12:44.723 position:50% align:center
Let me see. Where to begin?

00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:46.224 position:50% align:center
Ah, I know!

00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:49.686 position:50% align:center
It all happened a very long
time ago, when our village

00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:52.605 position:50% align:center
was still split into two
different places--

00:12:52.689 --> 00:12:58.111 position:50% align:center
That Village and This Village--
and all we ever did was fight.

00:12:58.194 --> 00:13:00.864 position:50% align:center
One day, we had
a special visitor.

00:13:00.947 --> 00:13:05.243 position:50% align:center
She was a traveling witch,
and a major part of our history.

00:13:13.126 --> 00:13:14.252 position:50% align:center
[FORMER VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Welcome to "This Village,"

00:13:14.336 --> 00:13:15.253 position:50% align:center
Madam witch!

00:13:15.337 --> 00:13:16.963 position:50% align:center
Is that its real name?

00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:19.257 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Yes! See, our village is called

00:13:19.341 --> 00:13:21.801 position:50% align:center
"This Village," but should you
venture onto the other side

00:13:21.885 --> 00:13:24.971 position:50% align:center
of the road, then you'll find
yourself in "That Village."

00:13:25.055 --> 00:13:26.473 position:50% align:center
Oh, I've heard of you!

00:13:26.556 --> 00:13:29.351 position:50% align:center
This and That Villages are
famous for their wine, right?

00:13:29.434 --> 00:13:30.435 position:50% align:center
Indeed!

00:13:30.518 --> 00:13:32.896 position:50% align:center
It's been our specialty
for many years.

00:13:32.979 --> 00:13:35.648 position:50% align:center
So, madam witch. Do you
enjoy a good vintage?

00:13:35.732 --> 00:13:39.069 position:50% align:center
I've never had any before.
That's why I traveled here.

00:13:39.152 --> 00:13:39.944 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Hm?

00:13:40.028 --> 00:13:41.863 position:50% align:center
It will be my very first drink,

00:13:41.946 --> 00:13:44.908 position:50% align:center
so I wanted to make sure that
it was something memorable.

00:13:44.991 --> 00:13:46.409 position:50% align:center
Well, no worries there.

00:13:46.493 --> 00:13:48.161 position:50% align:center
You came to exactly
the right place

00:13:48.244 --> 00:13:49.579 position:50% align:center
if that's what you're after.

00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:51.206 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Our wine is far superior

00:13:51.289 --> 00:13:53.375 position:50% align:center
to what they make
in "That Village."

00:13:53.458 --> 00:13:56.795 position:50% align:center
It is truly the
nectar of the gods!

00:13:56.878 --> 00:13:58.755 position:50% align:center
That's quite a statement.

00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:01.049 position:50% align:center
So, is that the wine
you boast of?

00:14:01.132 --> 00:14:03.009 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Oh! Um, no.

00:14:03.093 --> 00:14:06.179 position:50% align:center
This wine is actually
from That Village.

00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:10.225 position:50% align:center
Yes! In their desperate bid
to increase their sales of it,

00:14:10.308 --> 00:14:12.227 position:50% align:center
they had the nerve to do this!

00:14:12.310 --> 00:14:17.273 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] "Grape-stomping maiden,
Rosemary, from That Village."

00:14:17.357 --> 00:14:18.983 position:50% align:center
And there's a quote
from her saying,

00:14:19.067 --> 00:14:21.945 position:50% align:center
"I lovingly stepped
on every grape."

00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:24.072 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A] The
worst part is that it's working.

00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:26.616 position:50% align:center
This label of the lovely
Rosemary has indeed

00:14:26.700 --> 00:14:28.660 position:50% align:center
driven their sales
up significantly.

00:14:28.743 --> 00:14:30.203 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Uh...

00:14:30.286 --> 00:14:31.663 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A] If
That Village is to be believed,

00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:34.332 position:50% align:center
Rosemary herself is the
wine's "place of origin."

00:14:34.416 --> 00:14:35.792 position:50% align:center
It's "place of origin?"

00:14:35.875 --> 00:14:37.043 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
That's right.

00:14:37.127 --> 00:14:39.129 position:50% align:center
Not the one who made it,
but where it came from?

00:14:39.212 --> 00:14:40.839 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A] They
know suggesting something

00:14:40.922 --> 00:14:43.299 position:50% align:center
like that will tempt
more people to buy it.

00:14:43.383 --> 00:14:44.342 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
But how?

00:14:44.426 --> 00:14:45.760 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A
clears throat]

00:14:45.844 --> 00:14:48.138 position:50% align:center
Well, quite frankly, customers
have certain fetishes,

00:14:48.221 --> 00:14:50.140 position:50% align:center
and appealing to them
is an important aspect

00:14:50.223 --> 00:14:51.683 position:50% align:center
of any business.

00:14:51.766 --> 00:14:54.936 position:50% align:center
So, I take it it's selling well?

00:14:55.020 --> 00:14:56.396 position:50% align:center
Only because a beautiful woman

00:14:56.479 --> 00:14:58.064 position:50% align:center
is stepping lovingly
on their grapes!

00:14:58.148 --> 00:15:00.150 position:50% align:center
"Stepping lovingly."

00:15:00.233 --> 00:15:02.277 position:50% align:center
Well, then, why doesn't
This Village get

00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:03.820 position:50% align:center
a beautiful woman of its own?

00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.238 position:50% align:center
Yes! One who can step

00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:08.324 position:50% align:center
just as lovingly upon
grapes as Rosemary.

00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:10.368 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
You're a genius!

00:15:10.452 --> 00:15:11.995 position:50% align:center
It's true! That's what we need.

00:15:12.078 --> 00:15:14.706 position:50% align:center
If we get a sweet maiden to
step lovingly on our grapes,

00:15:14.789 --> 00:15:17.000 position:50% align:center
then we'll crush the
competition for sure!

00:15:17.083 --> 00:15:21.338 position:50% align:center
And since it was your idea,
will you do us the honors? Well?

00:15:21.421 --> 00:15:22.714 position:50% align:center
Uh...

00:15:22.797 --> 00:15:24.382 position:50% align:center
Everybody! Madam witch said

00:15:24.466 --> 00:15:27.177 position:50% align:center
she'll step lovingly
on our grapes all day!

00:15:27.260 --> 00:15:28.970 position:50% align:center
[MEN cheer]

00:15:29.054 --> 00:15:31.431 position:50% align:center
[MAN 07B] A cute witch is gonna
step lovingly on our grapes!

00:15:31.514 --> 00:15:33.308 position:50% align:center
[MAN 07C] All right!
Will she step on me, too?

00:15:33.391 --> 00:15:37.145 position:50% align:center
[WOMAN 07E] They're making
complete fools of themselves.

00:15:37.228 --> 00:15:38.146 position:50% align:center
What a bunch of idiots.

00:15:38.229 --> 00:15:39.272 position:50% align:center
Um, wait...

00:15:39.356 --> 00:15:40.857 position:50% align:center
[MAN 07B]
We need to get her ready!

00:15:40.940 --> 00:15:44.235 position:50% align:center
[screams] Hey, put me
down, right now!

00:15:52.577 --> 00:15:54.871 position:50% align:center
Do I have to wear this costume?

00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:57.582 position:50% align:center
Yes! Don't be bashful,
madam witch.

00:15:57.665 --> 00:15:58.792 position:50% align:center
I asure you this is what

00:15:58.875 --> 00:16:00.710 position:50% align:center
all the best grape-
stomping maidens wear.

00:16:00.794 --> 00:16:03.213 position:50% align:center
It makes them more tempting.

00:16:03.296 --> 00:16:05.131 position:50% align:center
I'm not so sure.

00:16:05.215 --> 00:16:06.758 position:50% align:center
[MEN]
Ready, go!

00:16:09.719 --> 00:16:13.598 position:50% align:center
[ROSEMARY] Goodness,
whatever are you up to here?

00:16:14.849 --> 00:16:15.892 position:50% align:center
[ROSEMARY laughs]

00:16:15.975 --> 00:16:17.644 position:50% align:center
Well, hello there,
chief of the village

00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:20.313 position:50% align:center
that won't be around
for very much longer.

00:16:20.397 --> 00:16:21.606 position:50% align:center
It's really you,

00:16:21.690 --> 00:16:24.192 position:50% align:center
the beautiful grape-
stomping maiden Rosemary!

00:16:24.275 --> 00:16:27.195 position:50% align:center
[MEN]
The beautiful Rosemary!

00:16:27.278 --> 00:16:28.655 position:50% align:center
Oh, my. And what might

00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.615 position:50% align:center
that bottle you're clutching
to your chest be?

00:16:30.699 --> 00:16:31.700 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Oh, uh--

00:16:31.783 --> 00:16:34.661 position:50% align:center
It looks an awful
lot like my label.

00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:37.789 position:50% align:center
Could it be This Village's
chief's a fan of mine?

00:16:37.872 --> 00:16:39.457 position:50% align:center
Who, me? A fan of yours?

00:16:39.541 --> 00:16:41.126 position:50% align:center
No! Of course not.
I would never.

00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.585 position:50% align:center
Well, I would be
more than happy

00:16:42.669 --> 00:16:44.504 position:50% align:center
to sign the label if you'd like.

00:16:44.587 --> 00:16:45.922 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Really?!

00:16:47.757 --> 00:16:49.509 position:50% align:center
[ROSEMARY] Wait, who in
the world is this poor,

00:16:49.592 --> 00:16:53.847 position:50% align:center
undersized creature masquerading
as a grape-stomping maiden?

00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:55.724 position:50% align:center
A traveling witch, thank you.

00:16:55.807 --> 00:16:59.060 position:50% align:center
Oh. You're a witch?

00:16:59.144 --> 00:17:00.854 position:50% align:center
I think I understand.

00:17:00.937 --> 00:17:02.731 position:50% align:center
You're intimidated
by my success,

00:17:02.814 --> 00:17:05.567 position:50% align:center
so you've found someone to
step lovingly on your grapes.

00:17:05.650 --> 00:17:07.777 position:50% align:center
A pity she's so scrawny.

00:17:07.861 --> 00:17:09.571 position:50% align:center
Who are you calling scrawny?

00:17:09.654 --> 00:17:12.240 position:50% align:center
Such a plain face,

00:17:12.323 --> 00:17:14.576 position:50% align:center
A plain face, huh?

00:17:14.659 --> 00:17:17.287 position:50% align:center
Honestly, her figure's
just like a child's.

00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:19.581 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] Okay, now
you've taken it too far.

00:17:19.664 --> 00:17:22.834 position:50% align:center
No, wait. She's not like
a child, she actually is one.

00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:24.753 position:50% align:center
You convinced a child
to play dress-up

00:17:24.836 --> 00:17:26.504 position:50% align:center
and step lovingly
on some grapes,

00:17:26.588 --> 00:17:28.673 position:50% align:center
and you think that's
enough to beat me?

00:17:28.757 --> 00:17:30.050 position:50% align:center
[laughs]

00:17:30.133 --> 00:17:30.884 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA growls]

00:17:30.967 --> 00:17:32.552 position:50% align:center
Sorry, I have to go.

00:17:32.635 --> 00:17:34.596 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MEN] ...and step
and step and step and step

00:17:34.679 --> 00:17:37.474 position:50% align:center
and step and step and
step and step and step...

00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:40.101 position:50% align:center
You know what, Chief?
You can count me in.

00:17:40.185 --> 00:17:41.436 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:17:43.021 --> 00:17:45.148 position:50% align:center
I'm your grape-stomping maiden!

00:17:45.231 --> 00:17:47.734 position:50% align:center
[MEN]
Yeah!

00:17:52.489 --> 00:17:53.907 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA inhales]

00:17:53.990 --> 00:18:03.416 position:50% align:center
--Die! Die! Die! Die! Die!
--[MEN] Step! Step! Step! Step!

00:18:03.500 --> 00:18:05.835 position:50% align:center
[WOMEN]
Step... step... and step...

00:18:15.679 --> 00:18:17.722 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
I'm exhausted.

00:18:17.806 --> 00:18:20.308 position:50% align:center
You truly did an
excellent job, Madam Witch.

00:18:20.392 --> 00:18:23.436 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA] I feel like I stomped
about a million grapes today.

00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:26.523 position:50% align:center
So, how much wine do you
think it'll end up making?

00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.066 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
Let's see...

00:18:28.149 --> 00:18:30.485 position:50% align:center
I would say we're looking
at around half a cask.

00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:31.486 position:50% align:center
That's it?

00:18:31.569 --> 00:18:33.988 position:50% align:center
Even after all
that stomping? Ugh.

00:18:34.072 --> 00:18:35.657 position:50% align:center
The life of a
grape-stomping maiden's

00:18:35.740 --> 00:18:37.701 position:50% align:center
certainly not an easy one.

00:18:39.202 --> 00:18:42.872 position:50% align:center
What about that stuff?
How much have they sold?

00:18:42.956 --> 00:18:46.042 position:50% align:center
Well, I'm not sure of the
exact number, but it's a lot.

00:18:46.126 --> 00:18:48.545 position:50% align:center
Maybe even thousands
of bottles by now.

00:18:48.628 --> 00:18:51.172 position:50% align:center
Based on today, I'd say
Rosemary would have to spend

00:18:51.256 --> 00:18:53.800 position:50% align:center
every waking moment of her life
stomping grapes in order

00:18:53.883 --> 00:18:55.677 position:50% align:center
to produce that many
bottles, and even then,

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:57.262 position:50% align:center
it might not be enough.

00:18:57.345 --> 00:18:59.097 position:50% align:center
Oh...

00:18:59.180 --> 00:19:01.975 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Does that seem strange to you?

00:19:02.058 --> 00:19:05.603 position:50% align:center
[THIS VILLAGE CHIEF 07A]
It does.

00:19:05.687 --> 00:19:09.899 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MEN] Step and step
and step and step...

00:19:09.983 --> 00:19:11.776 position:50% align:center
Come on now, boys,
I know you can stomp

00:19:11.860 --> 00:19:13.194 position:50% align:center
harder than that.

00:19:13.278 --> 00:19:16.239 position:50% align:center
Don't you wanna sell wine
with my lovely face on it?

00:19:16.322 --> 00:19:17.866 position:50% align:center
Then pick up the pace!

00:19:17.949 --> 00:19:21.119 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MEN] Step and step
and step and step...

00:19:21.202 --> 00:19:24.831 position:50% align:center
I'm beginning to think that
the wine in those bottles

00:19:24.914 --> 00:19:27.625 position:50% align:center
wasn't lovingly stepped on
by Rosemary, after all.

00:19:27.709 --> 00:19:30.420 position:50% align:center
Wow. You're a quick one.

00:19:30.503 --> 00:19:31.671 position:50% align:center
Wait.

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:38.261 position:50% align:center
[ELAINA]
Admit it.

00:19:38.345 --> 00:19:41.348 position:50% align:center
The wine's point of origin
has been misrepresented.

00:19:41.431 --> 00:19:44.351 position:50% align:center
This is the kind of case that
could be brought to court!

00:19:44.434 --> 00:19:45.935 position:50% align:center
[ROSEMARY grunts]

00:19:46.019 --> 00:19:47.354 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MEN sadly]
Step...

00:19:47.437 --> 00:19:49.439 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MAN 07A] Aw, jeez,
we've been found out, huh?

00:19:49.522 --> 00:19:50.899 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MAN 07B]
We were selling so many, too.

00:19:50.982 --> 00:19:52.067 position:50% align:center
[STRONG MAN 07C]
It's kind of amazing

00:19:52.150 --> 00:19:53.818 position:50% align:center
it took this long, actually.

00:19:53.902 --> 00:19:55.362 position:50% align:center
I can't believe it!

00:19:55.445 --> 00:19:57.697 position:50% align:center
The wine we thought was imbued
with the essence of Rosemary

00:19:57.781 --> 00:20:00.116 position:50% align:center
was in fact stomped by
the feet of those large men.

00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:01.534 position:50% align:center
Tragic!

00:20:03.203 --> 00:20:05.580 position:50% align:center
Why's it even matter who
stepped on the grapes?

00:20:05.663 --> 00:20:06.998 position:50% align:center
It tastes the same!

00:20:07.082 --> 00:20:09.250 position:50% align:center
Oh, my. I've never
had a glass of wine

00:20:09.334 --> 00:20:12.045 position:50% align:center
